              <h2>Mental Health America (MHA)</h2>
              <h3><a href="https://www.mhanational.org/">mhanational.org</a></h3>
              <h4>
                MHA provides educational materials on mental health conditions, screening tools, and resources for recovery. Explore their site to find information on mental health awareness and advocacy.
              </h4>
            </li>
            <li class="expandedLI">
              <h2>National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH)</h2>
              <h3><a href="https://www.nimh.nih.gov/">nimh.nih.gov</a></h3>
              <h4>
                Visit NIMH to access research-based information on mental health disorders, clinical trials, and scientific studies. This resource is ideal for those looking to stay informed about the latest developments in mental health research.
              </h4>
            </li>
            <li class="expandedLI">
              <h2>ADHD and You</h2>
              <h3><a href="https://www.adhdandyou.com/">adhdandyou.com</a></h3>
              <h4>
                This site offers resources specifically for individuals with ADHD, including educational articles, treatment options, and coping strategies. It provides information to help manage symptoms and improve daily functioning.
              </h4>
            </li>
            <li class="expandedLI">
              <h2>Autism Speaks</h2>
              <h3><a href="https://www.autismspeaks.org/">autismspeaks.org</a></h3>
              <h4>
                Autism Speaks offers a wealth of resources for individuals on the autism spectrum, including information on diagnosis, therapies, and support services. Explore their site to find tools and guides tailored to the needs of neurodivergent individuals and their families.
              </h4>
            </li>
            <li class="expandedLI">
              <h2>PsychCentral</h2>
              <h3><a href="https://psychcentral.com/">psychcentral.com</a></h3>
